<Author>Lollipop1971
<Content>A great find! We went searching for an alternative hotel after our original booking turned out to be almost 1.5 hours away from the city centre. After trying a number of hotels along La Rambla, we came across the Curious down a side street - and what a find. It's within 5 minutes walking distance from La Place Catalunia and about 15-20 minutes stroll to Port Vell - so a perfect spot, close to the famous market.This hotel is clean and well decorated. It's a 1* so doesn't have some of the extras we would normally like - such as tea/coffee making facilities and the breakfast is simple but as a base to enjoy everything Barcelona has to offer, it's great! We stayed for 3 nights out of the 4 we were away for and were moved from the very small 'double' to a twin room at the suggestion of the staff for the last 2 nights, when the room became free. The doubles are very small, so I'd recommend trying for a twin. The three staff we met were all great, helpful and informative.Definitely one to recommend. 
