<Author>trave_by_Donkey
<Content>Basic but v. modern, clean and superb location Stayed at Hotel Curious during the Sonar festival and have only good things to say. It's at the cheaper end so you know it's not going to provide luxury, but you hope it will be clean, quite, comfortable and have polite friendly staff - and all these hopes we're fullfilled! We had a room on the street side a few floors up, this gave us a small balcony from which to observer the constant activity of the narrow, atmoshpheric, typical-of-Barcelona Carrer below. With the French doors closed and the aircon on we couldn't hear any commotion. The bathroom was also very modern and clean.Arguably the greatest asset is the hotel's location though, on the slightly less touristy side of La Ramba. The streets here are lined with odder shops, restaurants and bars and there is far more real life and atmosphere on this side than on the more touristy East side where the Cathedral is. The huge food market is just round the corner as is the MACCBA centre of contemporary art. And there are loads of places to take advantage of a menu del dia sitting out on the pavement.So if you want a cheap hotel that is everthing a cheap hotel should be and is superbly located, give this some consideration. 
